<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States.</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-09-19"><hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Jackson reports the presentation of his letters on September 19, and
                            states that the Prince of Bulgaria expressed pleasure at the
                            establishment of direct diplomatic relations, and hopes that increased
                            commercial intercourse will result.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>